div1.p:
He called
James Honybourn
, who had known him six years;
Robert Jordan
, twenty;
James Steel
, nine;
John Reeves
, about three;
Francis Clairidge
, twenty three;
Richard Nusham
, twenty; and Mr. Brooks, about three years, who all gave him a good character. - He call'd also his brother
William Hunt
, who gave him the same, and further deposed, that the prisoner had an estate of twelve pounds a year at Watford, and a house at Whetstone, where he lives, one part of which he lets for seven pounds a year; he has also an income by his wife of four shillings per week, and a couple of other little tenements; that he is very well situated, has a very good trade, and under no necessity, as to his circumstances in life, to be guilty of such a thing as is laid to his charge.
